    3. Gluten Free Avocado Chipotle Sauce

Gluten Free Avocado Chipotle Sauce

   Post by [41]Cinde
     * recipe image cover

     * recipe image cover

   [42]

   BOOKMARK
   [43]

   PRINT
   (BUTTON)

   SHARE
   DELICIOUS

Description

   Here is a delicious gluten free Avocado Chipotle Sauce that is super
   easy to make and a welcome change from store bought guacamole. Chipotle
   chiles, smoked jalapeno peppers in adobo sauce, give this sauce a nice
   bite. Chipotle chiles are most commonly prepared in adobo sauce and
   sold in small tins. They are available in specialty stores and not all
   brands are gluten free. LeCosteña brand of chipotle chiles in adobo
   sauce is gluten free.

   Serve this Avocado Chipotle Sauce with grilled shrimp for a fabulous
   appetizer or entree. The sauce can also be served with grilled or raw
   vegetables, I like serving it with jicama sticks, or gluten free
   tortilla chips.

   You can change the presentation by serving a portion in a martini glass
   with shrimp around the edge or in a shooter glass with one shrimp
   resting on the top. No matter how you serve it I guarantee it will
   disappear before your eyes.

Ingredients

   1 avocado, mashed
   1 chipotle pepper in adobo sauce (1 tsp chipotle puree)
   1 Tbsp plus 2 tsp lime juice
   2 tsp white wine vinegar
   ½ cup plain lowfat yogurt
   1½ tsp ground cumin
   1 tsp coarse salt
   ¼ cup extra virgin olive oil
   ½ cup firmly packed fresh cilantro
   * Click to ingredient to choose one

Directions

   1
          Puree all ingredients in a food processor or with a hand
          blender. Serve with grilled shrimp, sticks of jicama or gluten
          free tortilla chips.

